data.meta_description: King Andreas II "of Jerusalem" Arpad of Hungary was born in the year 1175 in Esztergom, Komarom-Esztergom, Hungary, son of Béla III Arpad, King of Hungary & Croatia and Agnes of de Châtillon. He was married  to Yolande Courtenay, Princess of Constantinople, Countess of Courtenay, Queen of Hungary, they gave birth to 1 child., they gave birth to 1 child. He was married  to Beatrix D' Este, they had 5 children. He died on October 26, 1235 in Eger, Heves, Hungary. This information is part of Family tree Cromer/Russell/Buck/Pratt by Elizabeth Cromer on Genealogy Online.
